<subSubSection id="DA22AD6E638DE9134839535E367F5220" pageId="0" pageNumber="197" type="description">
<paragraph id="407887A958FA654C24E4ACCDEF831B01" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">Measurements.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="10888860CF80212B4D7D2B7597B25750" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">
Total length: male 3.90-4.31 mm (
<emphasis id="A54DF9C0809F176F08B013024A1F6813" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">N</emphasis>
= 18), female 4.31-4.75 mm (
<emphasis id="C2E0BA4A78481CF65A78E6284A6033AB" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">N</emphasis>
= 31).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="7132C86D2EE7A048D21D457CA7D43662" pageId="0" pageNumber="197" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="7E2D472996FE4BD5DEEDEF5E436B383F" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="716E982E5A467CF9B5E88B1D010970E6" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">
The salient features of the new species include: frons (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="1DEB7D3A4E7AF90618E852AD3DC38D57" captionStart="Figures 9–19" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 9 - 19. Metanigrus chromus sp. nov., male 9 head and thorax, dorsal view 10 frons, ventral view 11 tegmina 12 wing 13, 16 pygofer, lateral view 14, 17 gonostyli and pygofer, ventral view 15 aedeagus, left lateral view 18 gonostyli, dorsal view 19 aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1024.62226.figures9-19" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/520804" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">10</figureCitation>
) with two brownish-black patches on both sides; outer process of gonostyli (Figs 
<figureCitation id="682DEFA73E5368E71E08FF7DBC99DEBC" captionStart="Figures 9–19" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 9 - 19. Metanigrus chromus sp. nov., male 9 head and thorax, dorsal view 10 frons, ventral view 11 tegmina 12 wing 13, 16 pygofer, lateral view 14, 17 gonostyli and pygofer, ventral view 15 aedeagus, left lateral view 18 gonostyli, dorsal view 19 aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1024.62226.figures9-19" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/520804" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">13</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="4A00826D7F56EB1C6C47985E1B7BF4C1" captionStart="Figures 9–19" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 9 - 19. Metanigrus chromus sp. nov., male 9 head and thorax, dorsal view 10 frons, ventral view 11 tegmina 12 wing 13, 16 pygofer, lateral view 14, 17 gonostyli and pygofer, ventral view 15 aedeagus, left lateral view 18 gonostyli, dorsal view 19 aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1024.62226.figures9-19" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/520804" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">16</figureCitation>
) differentiated into two processes nearly equal at apex in lateral view; only basolateral side of anal tube (Figs 
<figureCitation id="96BEB004716F7B2540ADDF798AA30902" captionStart="Figures 9–19" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 9 - 19. Metanigrus chromus sp. nov., male 9 head and thorax, dorsal view 10 frons, ventral view 11 tegmina 12 wing 13, 16 pygofer, lateral view 14, 17 gonostyli and pygofer, ventral view 15 aedeagus, left lateral view 18 gonostyli, dorsal view 19 aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1024.62226.figures9-19" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/520804" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">13</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="858B6AF1F182049EF57028C5F0A0EC8F" captionStart="Figures 9–19" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 9 - 19. Metanigrus chromus sp. nov., male 9 head and thorax, dorsal view 10 frons, ventral view 11 tegmina 12 wing 13, 16 pygofer, lateral view 14, 17 gonostyli and pygofer, ventral view 15 aedeagus, left lateral view 18 gonostyli, dorsal view 19 aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1024.62226.figures9-19" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/520804" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">16</figureCitation>
) with a finger-like process.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="9135A4EAFC76B795B2E25290DDA29BAE" pageId="0" pageNumber="197" type="coloration">
<paragraph id="CF9145D13C519AE9681F72E9B0D2373C" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">Coloration.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7C6E3901FD7468BB27CE8E1C1ACFE65A" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">
General color grayish yellow (Figs 
<figureCitation id="169ACCA5161078388B615384B8A40E59" captionStart="Figures 1–8" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 8. Metanigrus chromus sp. nov., male 1 dorsal view 2 lateral view. Metanigrus guttatus sp. nov., male 3 dorsal view 4 lateral view. Metanigrus gremius sp. nov., male 5 dorsal view 6 lateral view. Metanigrus spinatus sp. nov., male 7 dorsal view 8 lateral view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1024.62226.figures1-8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/520803" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="17789C0F9E5BD747CDA76F5ADABC61FF" captionStart="Figures 1–8" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 8. Metanigrus chromus sp. nov., male 1 dorsal view 2 lateral view. Metanigrus guttatus sp. nov., male 3 dorsal view 4 lateral view. Metanigrus gremius sp. nov., male 5 dorsal view 6 lateral view. Metanigrus spinatus sp. nov., male 7 dorsal view 8 lateral view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1024.62226.figures1-8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/520803" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">2</figureCitation>
). Vertex yellowish white. Eyes blackish red. Frons whitish yellow, a yellowish-brown stripe in middle, with two brownish-black patches on both sides. Clypeus black-brown. Pronotum sublaterally with brownish-black patches. Mesonotum yellowish brown, with brown stripe medially. Legs yellowish brown. Tegmen hyaline, veins brownish. Wings semitransparent. Abdomen brown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="002BA358F422BDE9E3AF7957ABBC84A1" pageId="0" pageNumber="197" type="head and thorax">
<paragraph id="315FE7A868C03450F936E944D33B60A7" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">Head and thorax.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C523550324991BF65C2FC3D060BFDC81" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">
Head (Figs 
<figureCitation id="6C630F723F98CB451113E34643874C11" captionStart="Figures 1–8" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 8. Metanigrus chromus sp. nov., male 1 dorsal view 2 lateral view. Metanigrus guttatus sp. nov., male 3 dorsal view 4 lateral view. Metanigrus gremius sp. nov., male 5 dorsal view 6 lateral view. Metanigrus spinatus sp. nov., male 7 dorsal view 8 lateral view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1024.62226.figures1-8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/520803" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="23FF7ADBCA5B12980019D903D3F5D81C" captionStart="Figures 9–19" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 9 - 19. Metanigrus chromus sp. nov., male 9 head and thorax, dorsal view 10 frons, ventral view 11 tegmina 12 wing 13, 16 pygofer, lateral view 14, 17 gonostyli and pygofer, ventral view 15 aedeagus, left lateral view 18 gonostyli, dorsal view 19 aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1024.62226.figures9-19" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/520804" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">9</figureCitation>
) significantly narrower than pronotum, median carina absent. Vertex shorter in middle line than wide at base (1: 1.51), with two posterolateral areolets at base not meeting medially. Frons (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="6F86A9FA8800D092E97365BEFBAD184C" captionStart="Figures 9–19" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 9 - 19. Metanigrus chromus sp. nov., male 9 head and thorax, dorsal view 10 frons, ventral view 11 tegmina 12 wing 13, 16 pygofer, lateral view 14, 17 gonostyli and pygofer, ventral view 15 aedeagus, left lateral view 18 gonostyli, dorsal view 19 aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1024.62226.figures9-19" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/520804" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">10</figureCitation>
) subrectangular, without median carina, longer in middle line than wide at widest portion (about 1.45: 1), lateral carinae with a dense row of sensory pits along outer margin. Postclypeus (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="AA04BA3064C7332E153B6FFE59BA47BE" captionStart="Figures 9–19" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 9 - 19. Metanigrus chromus sp. nov., male 9 head and thorax, dorsal view 10 frons, ventral view 11 tegmina 12 wing 13, 16 pygofer, lateral view 14, 17 gonostyli and pygofer, ventral view 15 aedeagus, left lateral view 18 gonostyli, dorsal view 19 aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1024.62226.figures9-19" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/520804" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">10</figureCitation>
) with distinct median and lateral carinae. Frontoclypeal suture nearly straight. Rostrum elongate, surpassing hind-coxae. Pronotum (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="E789DF2749FE61F701A7315B5843CF43" captionStart="Figures 9–19" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 9 - 19. Metanigrus chromus sp. nov., male 9 head and thorax, dorsal view 10 frons, ventral view 11 tegmina 12 wing 13, 16 pygofer, lateral view 14, 17 gonostyli and pygofer, ventral view 15 aedeagus, left lateral view 18 gonostyli, dorsal view 19 aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1024.62226.figures9-19" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/520804" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">9</figureCitation>
) wider than maximum width of head (including eyes) (1.37: 1), lateral carinae sinuate, median carina present. Mesonotum (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="D4438687CBDE954828AB0C6489B45BBE" captionStart="Figures 9–19" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 9 - 19. Metanigrus chromus sp. nov., male 9 head and thorax, dorsal view 10 frons, ventral view 11 tegmina 12 wing 13, 16 pygofer, lateral view 14, 17 gonostyli and pygofer, ventral view 15 aedeagus, left lateral view 18 gonostyli, dorsal view 19 aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1024.62226.figures9-19" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/520804" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">9</figureCitation>
) about 6.14 times longer than pronotum in midline, with distinct median carina. Tegmina (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="F84B093252548D9354361E41CB575A41" captionStart="Figures 9–19" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 9 - 19. Metanigrus chromus sp. nov., male 9 head and thorax, dorsal view 10 frons, ventral view 11 tegmina 12 wing 13, 16 pygofer, lateral view 14, 17 gonostyli and pygofer, ventral view 15 aedeagus, left lateral view 18 gonostyli, dorsal view 19 aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1024.62226.figures9-19" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/520804" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">11</figureCitation>
) slender, longer than maximal width (2.41: 1), almost as wide at postnodal as prenodal area, veins ScP + 
<collectionCode id="D68B45318CAC88F59479B9D12FEDCA83" country="Chile" name="Departamento de Geologia, Universidad de Chile">R</collectionCode>
+ 
<collectionCode id="46A43789BCC19C36E2BE0D1068076EDF" country="0" name="Mohonk Preserve, Inc.">MP</collectionCode>
with several sensory pits, 
<collectionCode id="48DA0290AC546E0C58E3793BB4B75B44" country="0" name="Mohonk Preserve, Inc.">MP</collectionCode>
3 two branched; five postnodal closed cells with C1 smaller than C2, C5 placed next to C3, C4 distally displaced after the nodal line, im, r-m and anterior two-thirds of margin with white areas. Hind wing (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="C991D4C0C9EEF4F3DE91286B9BC47EE1" captionStart="Figures 9–19" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 9 - 19. Metanigrus chromus sp. nov., male 9 head and thorax, dorsal view 10 frons, ventral view 11 tegmina 12 wing 13, 16 pygofer, lateral view 14, 17 gonostyli and pygofer, ventral view 15 aedeagus, left lateral view 18 gonostyli, dorsal view 19 aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1024.62226.figures9-19" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/520804" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">12</figureCitation>
) with lateral margin notched at CuA1, CuP, and A2, more strongly at A1; A2 not reaching posterior margin. Metatibiotarsal formula: (3+5)-6-5.
</paragraph>
